OpenMAX core developed by Nokia and STMicroelectronics for Linux distributions

Major additions to the 0.3
- Component hierarchy architecture:
  - renamed base components
  - fixed several bugs on 0.2
  - tested on Fedora core 5
  - added new thread-mechanism for the message handling in the core
- The components of the 0.3 release are:
  - Mp3 decoder
  - Alsa sink renderer
  - volume control

Known issues:
  - several times the internal test suite (not published) hangs.
    Need more inspection

